ponent Interactions\n\n| Component | Purpose | Input | Output |\n|-----------|---------|-------|--------|\n| **Store Interface** | Abstract storage operations | Context, SessionID, SandboxInfo | SandboxInfo, Error |\n| **Redis Store** | Redis implementation using go-redis/v9 | Environment config | Store operations |\n| **Valkey Store** | Valkey implementation using valkey-go | Environment config | Store operations |\n| **Singleton** | Thread-safe provider initialization | - | Store instance |\n| **Key Builder** | Constructs Redis/Valkey keys | SessionID | Prefixed key string |\n| **Index Manager** | Maintains ZSET indexes | SessionID, Timestamps | ZADD/ZREM operations |\n\n---\n\n## Directory Structure\n\n```\npkg/store/\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ store.go              # Store interface definition\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ singleton.go          # Singleton provider initialization\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ store_redis.go        # Redis implementation\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ store_valkey.go       # Valkey implementation\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ errors.go             # Store-specific errors\nв””в”Җв”Җ doc.go                # Package documentation\n```\n\n---\n\n## Data Structures\n\n### Store Interface\n\n```go\n// Store defines the interface for session storage backends.\n// Implementations include Redis and Valkey providers.\ntype Store interface {\n    // Ping checks connectivity to the store.\n    Ping(ctx context.Context) error\n\n    // GetSandboxBySessionID retrieves sandbox information by session ID.\n    // Returns ErrNotFound if the session does not exist.\n    GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n\n    // StoreSandbox stores sandbox information in the store.\n    // Validates that sandbox is not nil and ExpiresAt is not zero.\n    // Uses atomic pipeline: SETNX + ZADD expiry + ZADD last_activity.\n    StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error\n\n    // UpdateSandbox updates existing sandbox information.\n    // Uses SET with XX flag (key must exist).\n    // Does NOT modify expiry or last-activity indexes.\n    UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error\n\n    // DeleteSandboxBySessionID removes a sandbox from the store.\n    // Uses atomic pipeline: DEL + ZREM expiry + ZREM last_activity.\n    DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error\n\n    // ListExpiredSandboxes returns sandboxes that have expired before the given time.\n    // Queries session:expiry ZSET with ZRANGEBYSCORE.\n    // Returns nil, nil if limit <= 0.\n    ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n\n    // ListInactiveSandboxes returns sandboxes inactive since before the given time.\n    // Queries session:last_activity ZSET with ZRANGEBYSCORE.\n    // Returns nil, nil if limit <= 0.\n    ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n\n    // UpdateSessionLastActivity updates the last activity timestamp for a session.\n    // Verifies session key exists before updating ZSET.\n    // If at is zero time, uses time.Now().\n    UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, at time.Time) error\n\n    // Close closes the store connection.\n    Close() error\n}\n```\n\n### Provider Type Constants\n\n```go\nconst (\n    redisStoreType  string = \"redis\"\n    valkeyStoreType string = \"valkey\"\n)\n```\n\n### Singleton Pattern\n\n```go\nvar (\n    initStoreOnce = &sync.Once{}\n    provider      Store\n)\n\n// Storage returns the singleton Store instance.\n// Initializes on first call using sync.Once.\n// Fatals on initialization error.\nfunc Storage() Store\n\n// initStore creates the appropriate Store implementation based on STORE_TYPE env var.\nfunc initStore() error\n```\n\n### Redis Store Implementation\n\n```go\ntype redisStore struct {\n    cli                  *redisv9.Client  // github.com/redis/go-redis/v9\n    sessionPrefix        string            // \"session:\"\n    expiryIndexKey       string            // \"session:expiry\"\n    lastActivityIndexKey string            // \"session:last_activity\"\n}\n\n// makeRedisOptions creates redis.Options from environment variables.\nfunc makeRedisOptions() (*redisv9.Options, error)\n```\n\n### Valkey Store Implementation\n\n```go\ntype valkeyStore struct {\n    cli                  valkey.Client  // github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go\n    sessionPrefix        string          // \"session:\"\n    expiryIndexKey       string          // \"session:expiry\"\n    lastActivityIndexKey string          // \"session:last_activity\"\n}\n\n// makeValkeyOptions creates valkey.ClientOption from environment variables.\nfunc makeValkeyOptions() (*valkey.ClientOption, error)\n```\n\n### Key Patterns\n\n| Pattern | Value | Description |\n|---------|-------|-------------|\n| Session Key | `session:{sessionID}` | Primary storage key for sandbox JSON |\n| Expiry Index | `session:expiry` | ZSET for expiry-based GC |\n| Last Activity Index | `session:last_activity` | ZSET for idle-based GC |\n\n### ZSET Score Semantics\n\n| Index | Score Source | Update Triggers |\n|-------|--------------|-----------------|\n| Expiry | `sandbox.ExpiresAt.Unix()` | StoreSandbox only |\n| Last Activity | `time.Now().Unix()` | StoreSandbox, UpdateSessionLastActivity |\n\n---\n\n## API Contracts\n\n### Environment Variables\n\n#### Redis Configuration\n\n| Variable | Required | Default | Description |\n|----------|----------|---------|-------------|\n| `REDIS_ADDR` | Yes | - | Redis server address (host:port) |\n| `REDIS_PASSWORD` | Conditional | - | Required unless `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false` |\n| `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` | No | \"true\" | Set to \"false\" to allow empty password |\n| `STORE_TYPE` | No | \"redis\" | Must be \"redis\" or \"valkey\" (case-insensitive) |\n\n#### Valkey Configuration\n\n| Variable | Required | Default | Description |\n|----------|----------|---------|-------------|\n| `VALKEY_ADDR` | Yes | - | Comma-separated list of Valkey addresses |\n| `VALKEY_PASSWORD` | Conditional | - | Required unless `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false` |\n| `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` | No | \"true\" | Set to \"false\" to allow empty password |\n| `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` | No | \"false\" | Set to \"true\" to disable client cache |\n| `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` | No | \"false\" | Set to \"true\" to force single client mode |\n| `STORE_TYPE` | Yes (for Valkey) | \"redis\" | Must be set to \"valkey\" |\n\n### Method Specifications\n\n#### Ping\n\n```go\n// Redis: PING вҶ’ expect \"PONG\"\n// Valkey: B().Ping() вҶ’ expect \"PONG\"\nfunc (s *store) Ping(ctx context.Context) error\n```\n\n**Success:** Returns nil  \n**Failure:** Returns connection error\n\n#### GetSandboxBySessionID\n\n```go\n// Redis: GET session:{id}\n// Valkey: B().Get().Key(key) вҶ’ bytes\nfunc (s *store) GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n```\n\n**Success:** Returns `*SandboxInfo`  \n**Not Found:** Returns `ErrNotFound` (Redis: redis.Nil, Valkey: IsValkeyNil)  \n**Failure:** Returns underlying error\n\n#### StoreSandbox\n\n```go\n// Atomically executes:\n//   SETNX session:{id} {json}\n//   ZADD session:expiry {expiresAt.Unix()} {id}\n//   ZADD session:last_activity {now.Unix()} {id}\nfunc (s *store) StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo) error\n```\n\n**Validation:**\n- Returns error if sandbox is nil\n- Returns error if sandbox.ExpiresAt.IsZero()\n\n**Success:** Returns nil  \n**Failure:** Returns error if any command in pipeline fails\n\n#### UpdateSandbox\n\n```go\n// SET session:{id} {json} XX\nfunc (s *store) UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo) error\n```\n\n**Semantics:** Updates JSON only if key exists (XX flag)  \n**Success:** Returns nil  \n**Key Not Exists:** Returns error indicating key not found  \n**Failure:** Returns underlying error\n\n#### DeleteSandboxBySessionID\n\n```go\n// Atomically executes:\n//   DEL session:{id}\n//   ZREM session:expiry {id}\n//   ZREM session:last_activity {id}\nfunc (s *store) DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error\n```\n\n**Success:** Returns nil (even if key didn't exist)  \n**Failure:** Returns underlying error\n\n#### ListExpiredSandboxes\n\n```go\n// ZRANGEBYSCORE session:expiry -inf {before.Unix} LIMIT 0 {limit}\n// Then GET each session:{id}\nfunc (s *store) ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n```\n\n**Parameters:**\n- `before`: Expiration threshold (sessions with ExpiresAt <= before are returned)\n- `limit`: Maximum number of results (returns nil, nil if limit <= 0)\n\n**Success:** Returns slice of sandbox info (may be empty)  \n**Orphaned entries:** Skips sessions where GET returns nil/empty (ZSET entry without corresponding key)  \n**Failure:** Returns underlying error\n\n#### ListInactiveSandboxes\n\n```go\n// ZRANGEBYSCORE session:last_activity -inf {before.Unix} LIMIT 0 {limit}\n// Then GET each session:{id}\nfunc (s *store) ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n```\n\n**Parameters:**\n- `before`: Inactivity threshold (sessions with last activity <= before are returned)\n- `limit`: Maximum number of results (returns nil, nil if limit <= 0)\n\n**Success:** Returns slice of sandbox info (may be empty)  \n**Orphaned entries:** Skips sessions where GET returns nil/empty  \n**Failure:** Returns underlying error\n\n#### UpdateSessionLastActivity\n\n```go\n// 1. GET session:{id} (verify existence)\n// 2. ZADD session:last_activity {at.Unix()} {id}\nfunc (s *store) UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, at time.Time) error\n```\n\n**Preconditions:**\n- Rejects empty sessionID\n- If at.IsZero(), uses time.Now()\n\n**Success:** Returns nil  \n**Not Found:** Returns `ErrNotFound` if session key doesn't exist  \n**Failure:** Returns underlying error\n\n#### Close\n\n```go\nfunc (s *store) Close() error\n```\n\n**Success:** Returns nil after closing connection\n\n---\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### Sentinel Errors\n\n```go\n// ErrNotFound is returned when a session is not found in the store.\nvar ErrNotFound = errors.New(\"store: not found\")\n```\n\n### Error Categories\n\n| Error | Usage | Mapping |\n|-------|-------|---------|\n| `ErrNotFound` | Session key doesn't exist | Redis: redis.Nil вҶ’ ErrNotFound; Valkey: IsValkeyNil вҶ’ ErrNotFound |\n| Nil Input Error | StoreSandbox called with nil | Generic error with message \"sandbox is nil\" |\n| Zero Expiry Error | StoreSandbox with zero ExpiresAt | Generic error with message \"expiresAt is zero\" |\n| Key Not Exists Error | UpdateSandbox on missing key | Generic error with message \"key not exists\" |\n| Connection Error | Backend unavailable | Wrapped connection error |\n| Pipeline Error | Any command in pipeline fails | First error from pipeline |\n\n### Error Handling Patterns\n\n#### Redis Error Mapping\n\n```go\nfunc mapRedisError(err error) error {\n    if err == redisv9.Nil {\n        return ErrNotFound\n    }\n    return err\n}\n```\n\n#### Valkey Error Mapping\n\n```go\nfunc mapValkeyError(err error) error {\n    if valkey.IsValkeyNil(err) {\n        return ErrNotFound\n    }\n    return err\n}\n```\n\n#### Validation Pattern\n\n```go\nfunc (s *store) StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo) error {\n    if sandbox == nil {\n        return fmt.Errorf(\"sandbox is nil\")\n    }\n    if sandbox.ExpiresAt.IsZero() {\n        return fmt.Errorf(\"expiresAt is zero\")\n    }\n    // ... store logic\n}\n```\n\n#### Existence Check Pattern\n\n```go\nfunc (s *store) UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, at time.Time) error {\n    if sessionID == \"\" {\n        return fmt.Errorf(\"sessionID is empty\")\n    }\n    \n    // Verify key exists\n    exists, err := s.cli.Exists(ctx, s.sessionKey(sessionID)).Result()\n    if err != nil {\n        return err\n    }\n    if exists == 0 {\n        return ErrNotFound\n    }\n    \n    // ... update ZSET\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n#### Interface Compliance Tests\n\n```go\nfunc TestStoreInterface(t *testing.T) {\n    // Test that both Redis and Valkey implementations satisfy Store interface\n    var _ Store = &redisStore{}\n    var _ Store = &valkeyStore{}\n}\n```\n\n#### Redis Store Tests\n\n```go\nfunc TestRedisStore_Ping(t *testing.T) {\n    tests := []struct {\n        name        string\n        mockPing    interface{}\n        mockErr     error\n        expectedErr error\n    }{\n        {\n            name:        \"success\",\n            mockPing:    \"PONG\",\n            expectedErr: nil,\n        },\n        {\n            name:        \"connection refused\",\n            mockErr:     errors.New(\"connection refused\"),\n            expectedErr: errors.New(\"connection refused\"),\n        },\n    }\n    // ... test implementation\n}\n\nfunc TestRedisStore_GetSandboxBySessionID(t *testing.T) {\n    tests := []struct {\n        name           string\n        sessionID      string\n        mockData       string\n        mockErr        error\n        expectedResult *types.SandboxInfo\n        expectedErr    error\n    }{\n        {\n            name:      \"found\",\n            sessionID: \"sess-abc-123\",\n            mockData:  `{\"sessionId\":\"sess-abc-123\",\"sandboxId\":\"sb-456\"}`,\n            expectedResult: &types.SandboxInfo{\n                SessionID: \"sess-abc-123\",\n                SandboxID: \"sb-456\",\n            },\n        },\n        {\n            name:        \"not found\",\n            sessionID:   \"sess-missing\",\n            mockErr:     redisv9.Nil,\n            expectedErr: ErrNotFound,\n        },\n    }\n    // ... test implementation\n}\n\nfunc TestRedisStore_StoreSandbox(t *testing.T) {\n    tests := []struct {\n        name        string\n        sandbox     *types.SandboxInfo\n        expectedErr error\n    }{\n        {\n            name: \"success\",\n            sandbox: &types.SandboxInfo{\n                SessionID: \"sess-abc\",\n                SandboxID: \"sb-123\",\n                ExpiresAt: time.Now().Add(time.Hour),\n            },\n            expectedErr: nil,\n        },\n        {\n            name:        \"nil sandbox\",\n            sandbox:     nil,\n            expectedErr: errors.New(\"sandbox is nil\"),\n        },\n        {\n            name: \"zero expiresAt\",\n            sandbox: &types.SandboxInfo{\n                SessionID: \"sess-abc\",\n                SandboxID: \"sb-123\",\n            },\n            expectedErr: errors.New(\"expiresAt is zero\"),\n        },\n    }\n    // ... test implementation\n}\n\nfunc TestRedisStore_ListExpiredSandboxes(t *testing.T) {\n    tests := []struct {\n        name           string\n        before         time.Time\n        limit          int64\n        mockZSetResult []string\n        mockGetResults []string\n        expectedCount  int\n    }{\n        {\n            name:           \"expired sessions found\",\n            before:         time.Now(),\n            limit:          10,\n            mockZSetResult: []string{\"sess-1\", \"sess-2\"},\n            mockGetResults: []string{`{\"sessionId\":\"sess-1\"}`, `{\"sessionId\":\"sess-2\"}`},\n            expectedCount:  2,\n        },\n        {\n            name:           \"orphan entries skipped\",\n            before:         time.Now(),\n            limit:          10,\n            mockZSetResult: []string{\"sess-1\", \"sess-2\"},\n            mockGetResults: []string{`{\"sessionId\":\"sess-1\"}`, \"\"}, // sess-2 is orphan\n            expectedCount:  1,\n        },\n        {\n            name:          \"zero limit\",\n            before:        time.Now(),\n            limit:         0,\n            expectedCount: 0,\n        },\n    }\n    // ... test implementation\n}\n\nfunc TestRedisStore_UpdateSandbox(t *testing.T) {\n    tests := []struct {\n        name        string\n        sandbox     *types.SandboxInfo\n        setXXResult bool\n        expectedErr error\n    }{\n        {\n            name:        \"success\",\n            sandbox:     &types.SandboxInfo{SessionID: \"sess-abc\"},\n            setXXResult: true,\n            expectedErr: nil,\n        },\n        {\n            name:        \"key not exists\",\n            sandbox:     &types.SandboxInfo{SessionID: \"sess-abc\"},\n            setXXResult: false,\n            expectedErr: errors.New(\"key not exists\"),\n        },\n    }\n    // ... test implementation\n}\n```\n\n#### Valkey Store Tests\n\n```go\nfunc TestValkeyStore_Ping(t *testing.T) {\n    tests := []struct {\n        name        string\n        mockResult  string\n        mockErr     error\n        expectedErr error\n    }{\n        {\n            name:        \"success\",\n            mockResult:  \"PONG\",\n            expectedErr: nil,\n        },\n        {\n            name:        \"timeout\",\n            mockErr:     errors.New(\"connection timeout\"),\n            expectedErr: errors.New(\"connection timeout\"),\n        },\n    }\n    // ... test implementation\n}\n\nfunc TestValkeyStore_GetSandboxBySessionID(t *testing.T) {\n    tests := []struct {\n        name           string\n        sessionID      string\n        mockData       []byte\n        mockErr        error\n        expectedResult *types.SandboxInfo\n        expectedErr    error\n    }{\n        {\n            name:      \"found\",\n            sessionID: \"sess-abc-123\",\n            mockData:  []byte(`{\"sessionId\":\"sess-abc-123\"}`),\n            expectedResult: &types.SandboxInfo{\n                SessionID: \"sess-abc-123\",\n            },\n        },\n        {\n            name:        \"not found\",\n            sessionID:   \"sess-missing\",\n            mockErr:     valkey.IsValkeyNil,\n            expectedErr: ErrNotFound,\n        },\n    }\n    // ... test implementation\n}\n\nfunc TestValkeyStore_UpdateSessionLastActivity(t *testing.T) {\n    tests := []struct {\n        name        string\n        sessionID   string\n        at          time.Time\n        exists      int64\n        expectedErr error\n    }{\n        {\n            name:        \"success\",\n            sessionID:   \"sess-abc\",\n            at:          time.Now(),\n            exists:      1,\n            expectedErr: nil,\n        },\n        {\n            name:        \"session not found\",\n            sessionID:   \"sess-missing\",\n            exists:      0,\n            expectedErr: ErrNotFound,\n        },\n        {\n            name:        \"empty sessionID\",\n            sessionID:   \"\",\n            expectedErr: errors.New(\"sessionID is empty\"),\n        },\n    }\n    // ... test implementation\n}\n```\n\n#### Singleton Tests\n\n```go\nfunc TestSingleton_Storage(t *testing.T) {\n    tests := []struct {\n        name           string\n        envStoreType   string\n        expectedType   string\n        expectedErrLog bool\n    }{\n        {\n            name:         \"default redis\",\n            envStoreType: \"\",\n            expectedType: \"redis\",\n        },\n        {\n            name:         \"explicit redis\",\n            envStoreType: \"redis\",\n            expectedType: \"redis\",\n        },\n        {\n            name:         \"explicit valkey\",\n            envStoreType: \"valkey\",\n            expectedType: \"valkey\",\n        },\n        {\n            name:           \"invalid store type\",\n            envStoreType:   \"invalid\",\n            expectedErrLog: true,\n        },\n    }\n    // ... test implementation\n}\n\nfunc TestSingleton_ConcurrentAccess(t *testing.T) {\n    // Verify sync.Once ensures single initialization\n    // even with concurrent goroutines\n}\n```\n\n### Integration Tests\n\n```go\nfunc TestIntegration_StoreOperations(t *testing.T) {\n    // Requires running Redis/Valkey instance\n    // Tests full CRUD cycle:\n    // 1. StoreSandbox\n    // 2. GetSandboxBySessionID\n    // 3. UpdateSandbox\n    // 4. UpdateSessionLastActivity\n    // 5. ListExpiredSandboxes\n    // 6. ListInactiveSandboxes\n    // 7. DeleteSandboxBySessionID\n    // 8. Verify deletion\n}\n\nfunc TestIntegration_ExpiryIndex(t *testing.T) {\n    // Tests that expired sandboxes are correctly identified\n    // 1. Store sandbox with short expiry\n    // 2. Wait for expiry\n    // 3. ListExpiredSandboxes should return the sandbox\n}\n\nfunc TestIntegration_ActivityIndex(t *testing.T) {\n    // Tests that inactive sandboxes are correctly identified\n    // 1. Store sandbox\n    // 2. Wait\n    // 3. ListInactiveSandboxes should return the sandbox\n    // 4. UpdateSessionLastActivity\n    // 5. ListInactiveSandboxes should not return the sandbox\n}\n```\n\n### Mock/Fake Implementations\n\n```go\n// FakeStore is a test double implementing Store interface.\ntype FakeStore struct {\n    mu        sync.RWMutex\n    sandboxes map[string]*types.SandboxInfo\n    expiryIdx map[string]int64      // sessionID -> expiresAt Unix\n    activityIdx map[string]int64    // sessionID -> lastActivity Unix\n}\n\nfunc NewFakeStore() *FakeStore {\n    return &FakeStore{\n        sandboxes:   make(map[string]*types.SandboxInfo),\n        expiryIdx:   make(map[string]int64),\n        activityIdx: make(map[string]int64),\n    }\n}\n\nfunc (f *FakeStore) Ping(ctx context.Context) error { return nil }\n\nfunc (f *FakeStore) GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error) {\n    f.mu.RLock()\n    defer f.mu.RUnlock()\n    \n    if s, ok := f.sandboxes[sessionID]; ok {\n        // Return copy to prevent external mutation\n        copy := *s\n        return &copy, nil\n    }\n    return nil, ErrNotFound\n}\n\n// ... implement other methods\n```\n\n### Test Coverage Goals\n\n| Component | Coverage Target | Focus Areas |\n|-----------|-----------------|-------------|\n| Store Interface | 100% | All methods |\n| Redis Implementation | 90% | Happy path, errors, edge cases |\n| Valkey Implementation | 90% | Happy path, errors, edge cases |\n| Singleton | 100% | Initialization, concurrency |\n| Error Handling | 100% | All error paths |\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n### Package Imports\n\n```go\nimport (\n    \"context\"\n    \"errors\"\n    \"fmt\"\n    \"os\"\n    \"strconv\"\n    \"strings\"\n    \"sync\"\n    \"time\"\n\n    redisv9 \"github.com/redis/go-redis/v9\"\n    \"github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go\"\n    \"k8s.io/klog/v2\"\n\n    \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types\"\n)\n```\n\n### External Dependencies\n\n| Package | Version | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|---------|\n| github.com/redis/go-redis/v9 | v9.x | Redis client library |\n| github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go | latest | Valkey client library |\n| k8s.io/klog/v2 | v2.130.1 | Logging |\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Notes\n\n### Redis Pipeline Usage\n\n```go\n// StoreSandbox uses pipeline for atomicity\npipe := s.cli.Pipeline()\nsetCmd := pipe.SetNX(ctx, key, data, 0)\nzaddExpiryCmd := pipe.ZAdd(ctx, s.expiryIndexKey, redisv9.Z{\n    Score:  float64(sandbox.ExpiresAt.Unix()),\n    Member: sandbox.SessionID,\n})\nzaddActivityCmd := pipe.ZAdd(ctx, s.lastActivityIndexKey, redisv9.Z{\n    Score:  float64(time.Now().Unix()),\n    Member: sandbox.SessionID,\n})\n\n_, err := pipe.Exec(ctx)\nif err != nil {\n    return err\n}\n\n// Check results\nif !setCmd.Val() {\n    return fmt.Errorf(\"session already exists\")\n}\n```\n\n### Valkey DoMulti Usage\n\n```go\n// StoreSandbox uses DoMulti for atomicity\nresults := s.cli.DoMulti(ctx,\n    s.cli.B().Set().Key(key).Value(data).Nx().Build(),\n    s.cli.B().Zadd().Key(s.expiryIndexKey).ScoreMember().\n        ScoreMember(float64(sandbox.ExpiresAt.Unix()), sandbox.SessionID).Build(),\n    s.cli.B().Zadd().Key(s.lastActivityIndexKey).ScoreMember().\n        ScoreMember(float64(time.Now().Unix()), sandbox.SessionID).Build(),\n)\n\n// Check for errors\nfor _, r := range results {\n    if r.Error() != nil {\n        return r.Error()\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### Key Construction\n\n```go\nfunc (s *store) sessionKey(sessionID string) string {\n    return s.sessionPrefix + sessionID\n}\n```\n\n### JSON Serialization\n\n```go\nimport \"encoding/json\"\n\nfunc marshalSandbox(s *types.SandboxInfo) (string, error) {\n    data, err := json.Marshal(s)\n    if err != nil {\n        return \"\", fmt.Errorf(\"failed to marshal sandbox: %w\", err)\n    }\n    return string(data), nil\n}\n\nfunc unmarshalSandbox(data string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error) {\n    var s types.SandboxInfo\n    if err := json.Unmarshal([]byte(data), &s); err != nil {\n        return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to unmarshal sandbox: %w\", err)\n    }\n    return &s, nil\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## File Index\n\n| Path | Role |\n|------|------|\n| `pkg/store/store.go` | Store interface definition |\n| `pkg/store/singleton.go` | Singleton initialization and provider selection |\n| `pkg/store/store_redis.go` | Redis implementation |\n| `pkg/store/store_valkey.go` | Valkey implementation |\n| `pkg/store/errors.go` | Sentinel errors |\n| `pkg/store/doc.go` | Package documentation |\n| `pkg/store/store_test.go` | Unit tests |\n| `pkg/store/singleton_test.go` | Singleton tests |\n| `pkg/store/fake_test.go` | Fake implementation for testing |\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/common/types/types.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/store/store.go":[]},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/session-store/design.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z